Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In January I caught a purse-snatcher who stole 's purse (30 points). Last Friday on a flight to LA, I stole the emergency flight information card (-40 points). In April I got in line at the supermarket at the same time as someone else and I didn't yield (-8 points). In July I saved a busload of nuns in Angola (326 points). Last Tuesday I donated bone marrow to in a life-saving procedure (300 points).

Overall, I've been nice (608 points). For Christmas I deserve a new dolly!

Sincerely,
scaramouch81

Write your letter to Santa! Enter your LJ username:

First posting in this journal in a long time and I had hoped for a more cheerful subject but I need to write about this.  Got a call yesterday morning from my friend whom I work with, one of our co workers died in her sleep the night before.  This came as one hell of a shock considering she was healthy, hadn't complained about not feeling ok (and she would have) and was only 58 years old.  My first reaction - oh shit! and really I'm still finding it difficult to move beyond that.  Her daughter, whom she lived with and was the one to find her, also works at our store and so even people who did not really know Flame, know Jackie and so most people have been pretty subdued these past two days. 

Its my first experience of death outside of close family and while I know you just react like you need to react its kind of hard in such a public setting - customers have been pretty cool about randomly wandering across people hugging and sniffling away in between clothing racks.  One of my colleagues, who had worked with Flame for longer is the same age and said she had difficulty sleeping last night 'cause she was afraid she might not wake up and I think that was true for many of the older staff members.

So in memory of a lady who could be a pain in the ass to work with but whom I genuinely liked as a person for her sarcastic sense of humour, her friendly approach to the newbies and her habit of calling us all 'love', I just wanted to say goodbye and goodluck in your next adventure.

Gakked from
blueraccoon

Da rules

1. Pick 10 popular songs that were your favorites when you were a teenager.
2. At least 3 of them must be songs you're embarassed to have really liked.
3. The songs must be part of pop culture.*
4. Write one full line from that song (e.g. "Love, I get so lost sometimes"). The line must be at least 5 words long, and "whoaaaa" doesn't count as one of them.
5. Can't use the same musician twice.
6. Post them here for everyone to guess.
7. Italicize and bold when someone guesses the song AND band correctly, and put who guessed it and the answer.
8. Looking them up (and then posting your answers) is, of course, cheating.
9. If people ask for a hint, give them the line before or after.

Hmmm...this is my first time posting on my livejournal and I'm not quite sure how everything works yet.  There's a very good chance that I may never post again seeing as I originally created the journal so I was graciously allowed access to several friends locked journals.  To those that friended me even without me having posted anything I thank you and do promise that I really am a nice girl - honest ;-P  Summer has arrived and I really wish it hadn't, I much prefer being cold to being hot.  If you're cold you can keep putting layers on, when you're hot there are only so many things you can take off and when you've got a figure like mine, there's even less.  Working for half a day tomorrow (Saturday) then spending the afternoon at the pool with friends.  I expect to have fun and come home sunburnt, my skin tends not to acknowledge the multiple layers of sunscreen I apply.  *shrugs* at least it will give my mum something to yell at me about on the phone later - why is it so hard to not mention these sort of things to your mother anyway?  I think I've babbled on quite enough so I'll be shutting up now.

Seeya
